pairwise interaction potential V(r) is detected** between the vortex centers in this regime. The motion of the vortices is likely dominated by advection from the large-scale turbulent background flow rather than direct vortex-vortex interactions.\n\n## 5. Summary Table\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Kurtosis | ' + str(round(kurtosis, 2)) + ' |\n| L├®vy alpha | ' + str(round(levy_alpha, 2)) + ' |\n| Hurst Exponent H | ' + str(round(H, 2)) + ' |\n| g(r) Peak | ' + str(round(gr_peak, 2)) + ' |\n| Force Exponent n | ' + str(round(force_n, 2)) + ' |\n| Size-Circulation beta | ' + str(round(beta, 2)) + ' |\n| Mean Lifetime | ' + str(round(mean_lifetime, 2)) + ' |\n| Energy Spectrum Slope | ' + str(round(e_slope, 2)) + ' |'
